4. Mean Value Theorem
    Proof.  
    $$
    \begin{align}
    &\ fa = ga\  \ \ \  \  
    & \ fb = gb 
    & \ hx = fx  gx\  \text{   define }hx 
    & \iff ha = hb = 0 
    & \implies  h'x = f'x  g'x
    & \implies  h'x = f'x  g'x = 0 \ \ \text{for some } x = c
    & \implies  f'c = g'c = \dfrac{gb  ga}{b a}
    & \implies  f'x = \dfrac{fb  fa}{b a}
    \end{align}
    $$

