The derivative

1. Derivative
    $$f'x0 = \lim{h\to\infty} \ \ \dfrac{fx0 + h ‚àí fx0}{h}$$

2. The forward/backward difference formula
    Derivative formulat at $$x = x0$$
    This formula is known as the forward difference formula if $$h > 0$$
    and the backward difference formula if $$h < 0$$.  

    
    



    Error Bound
        For small values of h the difference quotient $$\dfrac{fx0 + h ‚àí fx0}{h}$$ can be used to approximate $$fx0$$ with an error bounded by $$M\dfrac{|h|}{2}$$ where $$M$$ is a bound on $$|f''x|$$ for $$x$$ between $$x0$$ and $$x0 + h$$.

3. The $$n + 1$$ point formula to approximate $$f'xj$$
