4. Why Simple Zeros
    Quadratic convergence might not occur if the zero is not simple
    Example
    Let $$f x = e^x ‚àí x ‚àí 1$$ 
    Notice that Newton‚Äôs method with $$p0 = 1$$ converges to the zero $$x=0$$ but not quadratically


